The Kogi State Police Command has arrested six suspects in connection with the killing of the Peoples’ Democratic Party (PDP) Woman Leader, Mrs Salome Abuh, at Ochadamu, Ofu Local Government Area (LGA) of the state. The Kogi State Police Public Relations Officer (PPRO), a Deputy Superintendent of Police (DSP), William Aya, disclosed this while speaking with the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN), in Lokoja yesterday. Aya said that the suspects were brought in on Friday. Abuh, a former councillor and Woman Leader of the PDP was set ablaze on November 18 in her husband’s house at Ochadamu, by hoodlums. Aya said the police had started interrogating the suspects to ascertain their level of culpability in the murder of the woman. He said that the outcome of the investigation wound be made public as soon as it was completed. President Muhammadu Buhari had on Sunday directed the police to arrest the killers of Abuh with a view to bringing them to justice.